race.comment: WINNING EMOTIONS (16) impressed in all three runs this time in and looks close to a victory with the sharp weight drop. Circled the field with the big weight to finish a gritty third over 1100m at Goulburn. Gets map favours and sure to be thereabouts at the big odds. HIGHWAY STRIP (1) big class drop and is ready to deliver third-up. Snagged back from wide gate and never looked a chance with a poor ninth over 1200m at Randwick in BM78 class. Maps well and can finish over the top of these. ROSE AYE (11) tough mare struggling to draw a good gate. Showed plenty of grit when fourth over 1200m at Randwick in this grade. Near her top now and can run into the minor money. SOLITARIO (6) lightly raced gelding who looks forward enough for this first-up with the two trials. Strays in the mix. NEW PHAROAH (2) returned in good order and ticks a few boxes from the low draw.
